      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The scope of what they track is vast, extending beyond simple mood detection to encompass patterns of activity, sleep cycles, and even physiological proxies through connected wearables. To know for sure, you would need to examine the specific data collection policies and the underlying algorithms of each device, as the monitoring is often embedded deep within the software. You are right to feel apprehension; once these pervasive sensing networks are established, reversing that level of data collection becomes incredibly difficult.",
